The paper deals with metric-based algorithms and graph theory, which are topics commonly found in the arXiv CS sub-categories of Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM), Computational Geometry (cs.CG), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), Machine Learning (cs.LG), and Computational Complexity (cs.CC). The paper's focus on metric violations and approximation algorithms further supports these potential sub-categories.
